# Scenario: TEST-ACTIVATE QUOTA EXHAUSTED — Quectel BG96. SIM is in TEST-ACTIVATE
# state per Hologram dashboard. The customer transferred ~150 KB during testing
# without manually promoting the SIM to LIVE.
# Background:
#   Per https://docs.hologram.io/dashboard/sims/sim-states-and-statuses
#   TEST-ACTIVATE auto-converts to LIVE after 100 KB data OR 10 SMS messages.
#   But if the auto-convert event is delayed or fails, the SIM enters a state
#   where it CAN attach (test allowance is provisioned at the carrier) but data
#   packets are dropped/throttled at the Hologram core.
# Key signals:
#   +CEREG: 0,1, +CGATT: 1, +CGACT=1,1 OK, valid +CGPADDR  -- everything looks fine
#   +QPING: ALL packets time out (error code 569 = destination unreachable from
#   modem's perspective) — packets enter the network and never come back.
# Diagnosis: this is the SECOND silent killer. Modem says everything is healthy.
# Application log says "no data." The clue is "packet count = 0 returned."
# Customer guidance:
#   - In Hologram dashboard, go to the SIM, click "Activate" to promote
#     TEST-ACTIVATE -> LIVE, and assign a paid plan.
#   - Confirm SIM state via API: GET /api/1/links/cellular/{linkid}
#     Look for state == "LIVE" (not "TEST-ACTIVATE").
#   - After state change, allow up to 10 minutes for activation to settle, then
#     re-test the data path.
# Triage flag: if the modem looks healthy but data fails, ALWAYS check the SIM
# state via the dashboard/API before touching the modem.

AT+CPIN?
+CPIN: READY
OK
AT+CGDCONT=1,"IP","hologram"
OK
AT+COPS?
+COPS: 0,0,"AT&T",8
OK
AT+CEREG?
+CEREG: 0,1
OK
AT+CGATT?
+CGATT: 1
OK
AT+CGACT=1,1
OK
AT+CGPADDR=1
+CGPADDR: 1,"100.64.7.99"
OK
AT+QPING=1,"8.8.8.8",1,4
OK
+QPING: 569,"8.8.8.8",32,0,0
+QPING: 569,"8.8.8.8",32,0,0
+QPING: 569,"8.8.8.8",32,0,0
+QPING: 569,"8.8.8.8",32,0,0
+QPING: 569,4,0,0
